Olive Kitteridge (2008) is a novel by American author Elizabeth Strout. It presents a portrait of the title character and a number of recurring characters in the coastal town of Crosby, Maine. It takes the form of 13 short stories that are interrelated but discontinuous in terms of narrative. It won the Pulitzer Prize for Fiction in 2009 and was a finalist for the 2008 National Book Critics Circle Award. HBO is producing a mini-series based on the novel.